Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.82,0:00:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In tonight's Top Gear\Nfrom the Welsh forests,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.34,0:00:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Volvo's upmarket\Nnew hatchback, the 440.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.26,0:00:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They're catching the car,\Nbut who was the driver?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.26,0:00:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And how can you improve on\Nthe ultimate status symbol?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.77,0:00:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello and welcome to Top Gear.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.45,0:00:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,85)}We're at Dinas Mawddwy in deepest\NWales for the Audi Sport Rally.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.94,0:01:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,85)}Only a national event, but\Nit draws in a world-class field
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.82,0:01:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's the last major event before the Lombard RAC,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.02,0:01:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the British run, of course, of the World Rally Championship,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.70,0:01:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so it gives the champions a chance\Nto get to grips with the mud
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.86,0:01:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and the gravel of the British forests.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.62,0:01:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be looking at some of the rally\Nteams later on, but while we're tackling
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.86,0:01:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the early stages, let us look at a new car.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.87,0:01:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the Volvo 340 has been\Naround for some time, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.22,0:01:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's one of the great unsung\Nsuccess stories of the car market.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.30,0:01:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't the prettiest car in the world,\Nit's underpowered, doesn't handle that well
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.38,0:01:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but it goes on selling,\Nparticularly in this country,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.70,0:01:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,mainly perhaps because\Nof its reliability and its safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.66,0:01:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But now the Dutch factory of Volvo\Nhave brought out a new model, the 440.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.89,0:01:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It sits above the 340 in the range,\Nalthough it costs a great deal more,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.51,0:01:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and Chris Goffey has been\Nto Holland to try it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.72,0:01:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,GOFFEY: {\i1}Volvo's new 440\Nis a logical development{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.66,0:01:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}from the 480 sports car\Nthey launched last year.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.50,0:01:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's basically a saloon version of that car{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.30,0:01:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}with the same chassis and running gear.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.62,0:02:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}However, adding a saloon superstructure to\Nthe 480 has produced a slightly odd look.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.18,0:02:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}To my mind, the wheels seem too small\Nfor the rather dumpy-looking body shell.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.74,0:02:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Behind the Volvo badge on the front of\Nthis 440 and on the old 340 series cars is
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.30,0:02:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,a completely different factory to the\NSwedish Volvo that makes the 7 series and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.74,0:02:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the 240 Estates.\NThis is the Dutch concern
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.18,0:02:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that used to make the old rubber band\NVariomatic transmission DAFs,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.86,0:02:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Swedish company\Nonly has a 30% stake in this factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.74,0:02:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The British importer admits that he has\Nto do completely separate marketing deals
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.30,0:02:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,with the Dutch and the Swedes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.62,0:02:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But that said, there's no way that this\Nnew 440 cashes in on a Volvo image
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.90,0:02:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't deserve.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.46,0:02:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There's been tremendous attention to\Nsafety, as you'd expect with a Volvo.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.14,0:02:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Front and rear ends are crushable,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.02,0:02:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and there's an immensely\Nstrong passenger cage.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.54,0:03:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is the turbo version at the top of\Nthe engine range offered on the 440.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.26,0:03:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The engines themselves are built by\NRenault, and while they're close to the{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.46,0:03:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Renault 21 unit in most aspects,\NVolvo insists they're manufactured to{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.84,0:03:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}their own specifications.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.52,0:03:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}While there's a lot of headroom in the\N440, you feel that the seats are placed{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.78,0:03:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}close to the floor\Nof the car to achieve it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.48,0:03:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There's plenty of luggage space\Nunder the hatchback,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.30,0:03:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and the folding rear seats\Nare split asymmetrically.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.70,0:03:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This car was fitted with one of these\Ndreadful skinny space savers.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.66,0:03:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I hope the British importer goes for a\Nproper spare.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.50,0:03:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There's plenty of room for it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.55,0:03:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,On the road, this Volvo 440\Nis a brisk performer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.46,0:03:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There's very little road or wind noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.85,0:03:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The handling is precise,\Nsafe and reassuring.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.99,0:03:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This model's fitted with power steering as\Nstandard, and it gives you a very good
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.85,0:03:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,feel of what's going on at the front wheels.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.99,0:03:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Very impressive that\Ndespite being a turbo car,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.22,0:04:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,there's very little fight\Nor torque steer at the wheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.54,0:04:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Even when you apply\Nfull power on damp surfaces,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.38,0:04:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and the front wheels scrabble for grip.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.29,0:04:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Anti-lock brakes are an option.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.07,0:04:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A pity they're not standard.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.45,0:04:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But it's nice to see Volvo have gone for\Nclear and traditional dials rather than{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.73,0:04:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}fashionable digital readouts.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.14,0:04:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The real crunch will come\Nfor the 440 in Britain{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.82,0:04:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}when it goes on sale here next year.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.98,0:04:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The importers are emphatic that the car is\Nnot a replacement for the old 3 Series,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.63,0:04:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but will move up into the class above.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.27,0:04:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They're talking about the\NVolkswagen Passat, the Audi 80,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.61,0:04:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the top-of-the-line Ford Sierra, and the new\NVauxhall Cavalier as the car's competitors,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.07,0:04:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm not sure people\Nwill perceive the car in that class.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.21,0:04:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}To me, it still looks very much an\NEscort-sized package, and if that's how{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.35,0:04:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}potential 440 customers see it,\NVolvo may have problems.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.05,0:04:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Their owners have always appreciated\Na lot of metal for their money,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.75,0:05:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and the company may have\Nto work hard in the UK{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.46,0:05:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to convince people\Nthey're still getting it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.42,0:05:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So to sum up, the Volvo 440 Turbo\Nwe've been testing{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.46,0:05:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}has a 1721 cc engine, developing 118 BHP.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.94,0:05:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That takes it from 0 to 60 in under 9\Nseconds, and on to a claimed top speed of{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.16,0:05:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}125 miles an hour.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.58,0:05:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It won't be available in the UK\Nuntil spring of next year,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.94,0:05:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}when fuel consumption figures\Nand prices will be published.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.26,0:05:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we're sometimes\Ncriticized on this programme
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.66,0:05:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,for talking too much about cars' top speeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.62,0:05:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We do talk about them, of course,\Nbut it's worth saying in mitigation,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.78,0:05:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not because of any\Nglorification of speed as such.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.86,0:05:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We talk about speed because it's a very\Ngood way of defining a car's performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.72,0:05:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the fact of the matter is\Nthat the performance of most cars
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.78,0:05:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,with modern technology\Nis steadily being improved.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.26,0:05:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,There aren't many family cars,\Nfor example, that can't do 100 mph or more.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.06,0:05:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, the temptation is there,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.84,0:05:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,once the performance is there,\Nto use it as often as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.90,0:06:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, greater speeds, on crowded\Nroads, means greater danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.26,0:06:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why the police are\Nexperimenting with more efficient ways
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.02,0:06:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,of catching the lawbreaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.44,0:06:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}From a distance, this looks\Nlike any other Jaguar.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.64,0:06:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But take a look inside,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.16,0:06:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and it's a police motorway patrol car\Nwith the latest video camera on board.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.26,0:06:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Any driver thought to be driving\Ndangerously can be recorded on tape.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.72,0:06:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Perhaps the first he knows\Nof it being the blue light{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.50,0:06:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}flashing in his rearview mirror.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.54,0:06:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The driver can then be stopped,\Nand the tape played back to him.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.34,0:06:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,- Can you stand by the officer here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.34,0:06:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Just watch the screen, he will explain\Neverything to you, alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.78,0:06:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But the motorist isn't always stopped.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.22,0:06:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In the case of cars that go through\Ntraffic lights on the red,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.22,0:06:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}a camera can be installed\Nto take photographs automatically.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.70,0:06:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In fact, two are taken.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.36,0:06:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The first is triggered as the car\Ngoes through the red light.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.78,0:06:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The second proves that the car\Nactually crossed the junction.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.40,0:06:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there is another technique\Nthe police have been experimenting with
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.32,0:07:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,in various parts of the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.82,0:07:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a stills camera linked to\Na very accurate radar beam
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.78,0:07:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that can read a car's speed\Nvirtually instantaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.76,0:07:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So the equipment is set up\Non the side of the road
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.00,0:07:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,without the law having to be present.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.70,0:07:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever a car goes through\Nthe beam above the speed limit,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.82,0:07:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the camera automatically takes\Na photograph of it and prints out the speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.70,0:07:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and the date and the time as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.66,0:07:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So imagine the deterrent effect of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.18,0:07:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Photographic boxes set up alongside the\Nroad, motorways and ordinary roads,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.98,0:07:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,they wouldn't all have cameras in them,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.86,0:07:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but you wouldn't know\Nwhich ones didn't have.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.70,0:07:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So whenever you drove past\None above the speed limit,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.52,0:07:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd run the risk of being photographed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.70,0:07:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, all the equipment we've been talking\Nabout has been used in some countries
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.02,0:07:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,for several years now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.14,0:07:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's become a regular part\Nof traffic law enforcement.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.84,0:07:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are still several problems over\Nthe use of this equipment in this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.22,0:07:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,80)}At the present time, every time\Nwe take someone to court
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.06,0:07:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,55)}for the offense of excess speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.90,0:07:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to have a police officer\Nwho will state that the vehicle
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.16,0:08:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,was exceeding the speed limit and\Nthat is corroborated by other means.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.06,0:08:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,With the automatic camera, it requires\Nno human input whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.66,0:08:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,After setting the limits, it will keep\Ntaking the photographs
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.82,0:08:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,of speeding vehicles as they go by.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.86,0:08:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The general view is that currently,\Nin the case of speeding,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.58,0:08:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}photographic evidence taken\Nusing automatic equipment{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.58,0:08:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}without a policeman being present\Nisn't valid in the courts{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.82,0:08:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and therefore can't be used on its own.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.46,0:08:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There are other problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.78,0:08:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, under current law,\Nthe police can't send prosecution notices
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.26,0:08:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of speeding through the post.\NThey actually have to visit the driver.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.98,0:08:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So if the new equipment were introduced,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.58,0:08:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning many thousands\Nmore offenders were caught,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.94,0:08:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it would mean a massive increase\Nin workload for the police and could even
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.30,0:08:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,clog up the courts with motoring cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.18,0:08:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It raises the whole question of actually\Npinning down who was driving the vehicle
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.20,0:08:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time the offence was committed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.12,0:08:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,80)}- Putting to one side\Nfixed penalty offenses
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.58,0:08:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,80)}of not displaying\Nan excise license or parking,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.94,0:08:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,60)}the police have got to prove
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.58,0:08:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,80)}not only that an offense has been committed,\Nbut the person charged committed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.06,0:09:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So they will normally send to a\Nregistered keeper, a piece of paper saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.86,0:09:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,please tell us who was driving\Nat the time of the offense.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.06,0:09:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He commits an offense if\Nhe doesn't, and he could say,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.22,0:09:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but he can't get his license\Nendorsed for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.54,0:09:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But if he owns up and says it was me,\Nhe will get his license endorsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.26,0:09:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There's not, under a present law,\Nmuch of an incentive to him
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.64,0:09:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to own up and say it was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.12,0:09:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So if the police write to the owner\Nasking for the name of the driver{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.66,0:09:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and the owner refuses to cooperate,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.66,0:09:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}he wouldn't receive\Npenalty points on his license.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.42,0:09:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But just how much effort will the police\Nexpend in trying to identify the driver?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.28,0:09:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- Depends on the circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.10,0:09:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's a very serious case, then we\Nmay follow it up with a visit
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.44,0:09:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to the registered owner or ask\Nan adjoining police force to visit him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.88,0:09:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But of course, there has\Nto be a cut-off point.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.96,0:09:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,- In terms of effort alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.92,0:09:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- In terms of effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.24,0:09:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Our efforts are towards enforcing the\Nspeed limit and bringing people to justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.46,0:09:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And we would have to weigh\Nthe pros and cons of a particular case
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.84,0:09:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,before we went even further.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.70,0:10:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This begins to challenge, perhaps,\Nthe fundamental principle
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.44,0:10:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of innocence until proved guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.40,0:10:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are wider implications\Nbrought into the equation,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.98,0:10:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the infringement of civil liberties.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.98,0:10:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We welcome a system\Nwhich records offenders accurately.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.90,0:10:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,80)}But our concern is that we should have a\Nsystem which isn't also open to abuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.22,0:10:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,80)}For instance, for the police monitoring\Nthe whereabouts of citizens
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.74,0:10:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,55)}as they travel around the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.32,0:10:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And it seems to us that it is a case of\Ntechnology developing far more rapidly
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.46,0:10:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,than any safeguards to protect the public.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.16,0:10:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And is crying out for legislation\Nto build those safeguards in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.36,0:10:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, where does that leave us?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.98,0:10:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the report of the North Committee that\Nwas set up recently to examine traffic law
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.98,0:10:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,came out with three\Nunequivocal recommendations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.68,0:10:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They were that photographs\ntaken by automatic cameras
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.42,0:10:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,should be acceptable in court\Nas evidence of speeding.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.42,0:10:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That the penalty for not cooperating with\Nthe police in revealing the name of the driver
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.54,0:10:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,should be increased to include\Nthree penalty points in the license.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.48,0:10:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, the police should be allowed\Nto send fixed penalty type notices
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.92,0:10:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,through the post for speeding offenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.58,0:11:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, cut out a lot of police paperwork\Nand help to unclog the courts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.62,0:11:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But if these recommendations\Ndo come into force,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.16,0:11:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}what happens if the owner\Ndoesn't know who the driver was?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.98,0:11:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In, for example, the case of a company\Npool car used by several different drivers.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.50,0:11:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well, if the registered keeper doesn't\Nknow, or he can't remember, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.84,0:11:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,your worships it was a month ago,\Nhow can I possibly say now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.26,0:11:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he would be acquitted.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.46,0:11:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no question of a conviction.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.94,0:11:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But if a court thinks he's telling\Na pack of lies, he'd be convicted
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.18,0:11:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and penalty points\Nwill be awarded against him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.10,0:11:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- The implications of these potential\Nchanges seem disturbing.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.68,0:11:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The owner of the vehicle seeming\Nguilty until proven innocent.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.36,0:11:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But, of course, that has to be balanced\Nagainst the widespread concern{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.18,0:11:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to reduce the deaths and injuries\Non our roads each year.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.90,0:11:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, back here\Nat the Audi Sport Rally,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.14,0:11:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,speed is, of course, the essence,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.46,0:11:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,trimming that last tenth of a second of\Nthe time in the special stages.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.88,0:11:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the last round of\Nthe National Rally Championship,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.70,0:11:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's a big event in its own right.\NBut it's come to resemble a world-class event
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.10,0:12:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,because, as I said, so many of the\Ntop world stars use it as a practice
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.78,0:12:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,under British conditions before\Nthe rigours of the Lombard RAC.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.52,0:12:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,80)}{\i1}All eyes were on the\Nfour-wheel drive Toyota Celica{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.74,0:12:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,80)}{\i1}in the hands of former\NFord driver Jimmy McRae.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.94,0:12:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's the most likely car to beat the\Nall-conquering Lancia team next month.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.65,0:12:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Lancia have literally\Nswept the board this year{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.45,0:12:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and had the World Championship\Nsewn up by June in America.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.85,0:12:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So there wasn't much point in them\Nturning up for the Audi Sports.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.75,0:12:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}At the moment, Lancia lead Ford by nearly\N70 points on the table, an astonishing lead.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.37,0:12:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Audi are still in the frame,\Nthanks to the efforts of privateers,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.74,0:12:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}with Mazda trailing a poor fourth.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.43,0:12:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}McRae was putting up some\Nvery fast times in the Toyota,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.75,0:12:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}even though it was the first\Ntime he'd driven it in anger.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.26,0:12:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But then came problems.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.01,0:12:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- Well, the last two miles in the\Nlast stage, we had no rear brakes{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.43,0:12:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and we were taking it pretty easy.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.89,0:13:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But I think it's a good job that happened\Nbecause the front diff has gone{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.57,0:13:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and it's burst the casing of the gearbox.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.10,0:13:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So, I mean, it takes about an\Nhour and a half to change it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.39,0:13:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So we've decided that we're\Nnot going to go any further.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.11,0:13:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The lads will go back, change the gearbox{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.11,0:13:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and we'll get on with some\Nserious testing next week.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.07,0:13:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I mean, I was learning to drive the thing\Nand everybody was learning about the car.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.89,0:13:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So we're quite confident\Nthat the car is competitive.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.67,0:13:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We'll just go away now\Nand sort it out on our own.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.55,0:13:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,MASON: {\i1}Mazda have had a dreadful year\Nwith a whole chapter of mechanical failures,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.59,0:13:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}quite often related to the engine.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.34,0:13:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,60)}But mostly we have had engine problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.66,0:13:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,80)}And we are having 1,600 engines and it's a\Nlittle bit too small for this job.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.18,0:13:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have to try to get all the power\Nout of it, what we can get.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.53,0:13:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, that expense of\Nreliability sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.49,0:13:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,MASON: {\i1}Former world\Nrally champions Mikkola and Salonen{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.33,0:14:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}were again let down by their Mazdas,\Nengines and rear suspension this time.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.03,0:14:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Not a good omen for the Lombard RAC.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.90,0:14:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ford beat Lancia earlier this year \Non the all-tarmac Corsican rally,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.10,0:14:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but their two-wheel drive\Nwill be a problem in November.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.66,0:14:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}For veteran Stig Blomqvist, the Audi Sport was a chance{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.18,0:14:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to prove that he hadn't lost his speed,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.10,0:14:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but he could only manage\Nsecond place, poor by his standards.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.96,0:14:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But would you ever believe that this\NSierra went on to win its class?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.66,0:14:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Making its debut on this rally was\NVauxhall's new 16-valve engine,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.58,0:14:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but still only two-wheel drive.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.52,0:14:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Will this be a disadvantage?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.54,0:14:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,80)}Well, it's a big disadvantage\Nprobably on the RAC, yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.02,0:14:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,60)}because it tends to be very muddy and wet...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.14,0:14:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,80)}But hopefully, as I say, this will\Ndefinitely put us in the reckoning with
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.32,0:14:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,80)}all the other two-wheel drive\Ncars on the rally.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.54,0:15:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- Aren't Vauxhall just sort of treading water\Nfor the moment, ready for the Cavalier 4x4?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.52,0:15:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well, that's right. I mean,\Nthis car uses the same engine
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.86,0:15:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,as what we'll probably be\Nusing in the Cavalier 4x4
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.66,0:15:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's a good experience to get mileage\Nand et cetera on this particular engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.54,0:15:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And obviously we're very\Nexcited and looking forward
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.26,0:15:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to this new car that's coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.16,0:15:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,MASON: {\i1}The new engine\Ncame up with the goods.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.56,0:15:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Wilson set a scorching pace,\Nbeating many four-wheel drive cars{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.20,0:15:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to achieve third place overall.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.46,0:15:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Coventry's Peugeot team has\Nto combine its activities to Britain,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.79,0:15:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but has been going great guns this year,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.78,0:15:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}headed by the world's leading lady rally driver, Louise Aitken-Walker.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.93,0:15:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Seventh on this rally,\Nshe showed her magnificent drive{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.89,0:15:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}on last year's Lombard RAC\Nwas no flash in the pan.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.77,0:15:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Among the most unusual cars on the Audi\NSport was this tiny Nissan March Turbo.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.55,0:15:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Nothing to do with March racing cars,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.78,0:16:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}just a hotted-up version\Nof the Nissan Micra.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.95,0:16:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Under the bonnet,\Nthere's a tiny 988cc engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.03,0:16:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This has been given a turbocharger,\Nso it produces 130 brake horsepower.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.63,0:16:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you can see that the Japanese\Nhave actually found a way
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.66,0:16:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of putting a quart into a pint pot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.53,0:16:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Inside, it has all the rally car\Ntrappings, including a six-speed gearbox{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.33,0:16:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that looks a little like an oil rig.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.39,0:16:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Why aren't you driving a proper rally car?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.83,0:16:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- What bloody hell you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.65,0:16:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's a good car.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.07,0:16:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,60)}OK, this is a very small car.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.49,0:16:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,80)}This is really the smallest rally car,\NI think, in the Sport now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.45,0:16:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason is that people in Japan,\NNissan, like to try this car in rallying.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.73,0:16:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This is, you can say, a club car in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.83,0:16:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And we try to prove that you\Ncan even rally with a small car.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.15,0:16:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,MASON: {\i1}But never\Nunderestimate Per Eklund.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.77,0:16:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The jolly Swede pushed the Nissan\Nahead of many more powerful cars.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.99,0:17:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Another surprise of the rally\Nwas the performance of Ian Roberton.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.33,0:17:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}His old Nissan 240 charged round the route{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.58,0:17:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to clinch the British\NNational Championship.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.79,0:17:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He beat many more exotic\Nmachines into the bargain.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.83,0:17:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But at the head of the field, the vastly\Nexperienced Russell Brooks{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.41,0:17:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}was showing a return to splendid form,\Nbeating Blomqvist by nearly two minutes.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.07,0:17:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The old Brooks magic was still there,\Nso the Sierras could still be a force{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.29,0:17:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to be reckoned with\Nin November's big rally.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.35,0:17:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\u0}And maybe Russell's\Nold adversary, Jimmy McRae,{\u1}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.39,0:17:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}will regret his move from Ford to Toyota.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.29,0:17:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- We shall be reporting on the\NLombard RAC with two programmes,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.82,0:17:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,one early evening, one late,\Non each of the four days.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.25,0:17:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now to something which rally\Ncars tend not to suffer from
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.43,0:17:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're worked on so\Nintensively. I'm talking about rust.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.70,0:17:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Cars are certainly better made these days
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.79,0:17:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore they tend\Nto suffer from rust less.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.06,0:18:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The Swedes, for example, have\Ncarried out lots of surveys in this area
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.86,0:18:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and they've shown the\Naverage life of most cars,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.23,0:18:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,their average durability\Nis steadily improving.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.55,0:18:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,However, whether a car will rust\Nor not is certainly a major factor
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.99,0:18:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in deciding whether or not to buy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.54,0:18:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why, of course, many manufacturers\Nare now giving anti-rust guarantees.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.85,0:18:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The question is, do they stand up?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.86,0:18:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Tom Boswell has been casting his\Nmicroscope over the fine print of these
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.69,0:18:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,guarantees to see just\Nhow watertight they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.03,0:18:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,BOSWELL: {\i1}Rust is the\Ndread of the car industry.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.58,0:18:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Not so long ago, several manufacturers\Ngained reputations for producing models{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.87,0:18:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}which rusted faster than others.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.87,0:18:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Alfa Romeo, Datsun, Ford, Renault\Nand Talbot, to name but a few.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.06,0:18:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A rusty image isn't easily shaken off\Nand sales can be drastically affected,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.74,0:18:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}as Lancia discovered\Nin the 70's with their Beta.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.38,0:18:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now manufacturers give far more\Nconsideration to prevention{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.90,0:18:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}with improved paints and primers.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.06,0:19:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}More attention is paid to vulnerable areas\Nwith plastic, wax or other coatings.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.31,0:19:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Additions such as wheel arch\Nliners give extra protection.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.78,0:19:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Some even use galvanized panels.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.30,0:19:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,80)}The majority then back this up with\Nsome form of anti-corrosion warranty.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.70,0:19:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,These last from typically around\Nsix years up to ten years
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.89,0:19:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and Volvo recently have even\Nintroduced a form of lifetime cover.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.57,0:19:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Linda Zeff is one of several owners\Nwho feel they've been misled.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.47,0:19:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Her car was just four years old\Nwhen she first noticed rust.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.46,0:19:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well, when I bought the car, it came\Nwith a six-year anti-rust warranty.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.83,0:19:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,80)}And I took that to mean that the car\Nwouldn't rust within six years,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.05,0:19:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,60)}or if it did, the company would repair it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.21,0:19:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,60)}And it developed patches of rust
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.38,0:19:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and I took it in just over a year ago for\Nits anti-rust check, its annual check.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.82,0:19:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And was told that these particular patches\Nof rust weren't covered by the warranty
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.81,0:19:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,because this rust was rusting from the\Noutside in and not from the inside out
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.59,0:19:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore wasn't covered.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.29,0:19:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And obviously it's got\Nslightly worse since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.03,0:20:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- Did you read the rust guarantee?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.82,0:20:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- No, I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.57,0:20:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I assumed that the company was offering\Nsomething that was worth having.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.09,0:20:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn't occur to me that they were\Noffering something that had so many
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.89,0:20:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,clauses or get-out clauses.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.61,0:20:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,BOSWELL: {\i1}Most warranties refer\Nto perforation or rust-through.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.51,0:20:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This means a hole which\Nhas rusted from the inside.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.14,0:20:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Rusting on the outside surface from\Nscratches or stone chips isn't covered.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.86,0:20:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If it's not repaired at your expense,\Nthe warranty can become useless.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.10,0:20:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The most straightforward of these\Nanti-corrosion warranties include those
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.94,0:20:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,offered by Ford, Audi VW and Vauxhall.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.99,0:20:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They require no special re-treatments or\Ninspections, both common conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.98,0:20:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Otherwise, it's up to the owner\Nto ensure the car is presented on time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.10,0:20:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}for each and every inspection.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.14,0:20:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This usually is once a year,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.22,0:20:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}sometimes with a period of\Nlatitude as little as 14 days.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.55,0:20:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Washing the car may also be a\Nrequirement for which you have to pay.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.50,0:21:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When an inspection's carried out,\Nthe paperwork's most important.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.21,0:21:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}For example, Mitsubishi state:\N"You must ensure...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.07,0:21:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that the periodic body inspection record\Nis properly stamped and signed."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.58,0:21:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Re-treatments are required\Nby many companies.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.21,0:21:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They're usually needed at the\Nfirst, third and fifth years,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.75,0:21:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and it can cost up to £50.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.45,0:21:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Wear and tear doesn't just affect\Nthe polished surfaces.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.59,0:21:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Rusting due to scrapes, scratches and\Nchips underneath must be repaired,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.93,0:21:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}again, at your expense.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.81,0:21:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And that's not the end of the small print.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.78,0:21:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There can be some rather vague clauses.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.05,0:21:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Fiat stipulates: "Check and\Nclean the vehicle regularly."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.18,0:21:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"Keep the engine compartment clean."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.23,0:21:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"Check and clear all drainage holes\Nat the base of the door frames."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.18,0:21:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But what's meant by regularly?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.94,0:21:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And when did you last\Ncheck your drain holes?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.29,0:21:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Fiat say "the care and maintenance\Ninstructions are a sensible precaution to{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.05,0:22:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"prevent the neglect and abuse of a vehicle\Nand have never in fact been used to{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.97,0:22:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"invalidate the anti-perforation warranty."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.37,0:22:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Accidental damage must be repaired\Nto manufacturer's specifications.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.99,0:22:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If you apply your own\Nrust proofing to damaged areas,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.18,0:22:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}again, you're in danger\Nof ruining that warranty.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.71,0:22:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Besides Top Gear, the Consumers'\NAssociation is also concerned{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.13,0:22:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,about rust warranties.{\i1}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.58,0:22:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- They're very variable.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.15,0:22:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,60)}Some manufacturers are setting the pace
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.50,0:22:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,80)}with very good guarantees\Nthat require no inspections
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.30,0:22:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and don't cost the customer anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.98,0:22:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Others are lagging a long way behind that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.01,0:22:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And really could make\Nthe thing much simpler.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.74,0:22:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And they really should be\Nguaranteeing their product
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.34,0:22:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than depending on the customer\Nto do half the work for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.74,0:22:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- Are they using their small\Nprint in their guarantees{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.46,0:22:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to hide behind problems of their cars?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.63,0:22:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well, it's difficult to tell how much\Nthat's happening, but certainly a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.82,0:22:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,local agents seem to make it very\Ndifficult for the customer to actually get
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.17,0:22:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,a resolution of the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.67,0:23:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,When the local garage backs the customer\Nand takes the problem to the manufacturer,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.54,0:23:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,generally things seem to\Nget sorted out very quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.25,0:23:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's all to do with\Ncustomer relations and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.14,0:23:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,actually wanting the\Ncustomer to get a good deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.27,0:23:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And not everybody in the system at the\Nmoment is doing that well enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.79,0:23:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,BOSWELL: {\i1}Our advice is to read\Nthe warranty yourself before you buy.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.91,0:23:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If you have a problem, complain early\Nand stick to the same dealer.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.78,0:23:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And as the Fiat warranty\Nnow suggests, if all else fails,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.53,0:23:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}approach the manufacturer directly\Nor go to an independent arbitrator.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.54,0:23:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,One car that doesn't carry a rust warranty\Nis, would you believe, the Rolls-Royce.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.11,0:23:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No doubt they think it's beneath them
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.64,0:23:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,because, of course, a six-year-old\NRolls-Royce is scarcely run in.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.58,0:23:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the latest version of the ultimate\Nstatus symbol, the Silver Spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.73,0:23:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,£86,000 or new.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.82,0:23:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,For that, you get no fancy extras,\Njust the standard wrap-around leather,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.01,0:23:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the worn-up veneer and, of course,\Nthe spirit of ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.95,0:24:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, for many people, even this is too\Nplain a symbol of their power and prestige.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.26,0:24:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: {\i1}Customizing has\Nalways been a very dirty word.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.74,0:24:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You customize a Ford Capri.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.70,0:24:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You do not customize a modern-day\NBentley or Rolls-Royce.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.50,0:24:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What Hooper, bespoke coachbuilders\Nfor more than a century do,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.86,0:24:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}is Hooperise them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.32,0:24:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,80)}Now, this one, for instance, is seriously\Nlacking in the door department.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.94,0:24:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,80)}It began in life as a pretty standard\NBentley Turbo R with four doors
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.94,0:24:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and has been converted into\Nwhat's called a two-door coupé, i.e.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.02,0:24:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it has one long door on either side.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.06,0:24:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And that means there's pretty substantial\Nalterations between here and here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.64,0:25:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Moving further forward, you have\Ncolour-coordinated windscreen wipers.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.30,0:25:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They're very tasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.82,0:25:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And further forward still, we have a\Ncouple of air ducts in the bonnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.50,0:25:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Right at the front, only\Nthe badge escapes attention.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.92,0:25:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Square headlights will keep\Nour American friends happy.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.08,0:25:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And strangely, in a car with the\Naerodynamic properties of a wardrobe,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.62,0:25:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}they've seen fit to attach a spoiler\Nbeneath the rouged bumpers.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.98,0:25:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There's even a natty pair\Nof skirts along the side.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.50,0:25:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Finally, it's all topped off with\Nthese polished chrome wheels.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.95,0:25:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The modified Bentleys and Rolls-Royces\Ncome out of a North London factory{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.07,0:25:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}which specializes in fitting its own\Nbodies to someone else's wheels.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.33,0:25:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But how do you improve on what's widely\Nregarded as the best already?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.55,0:25:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The job's made even harder, because\Nin order to keep the warranty intact,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.11,0:25:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}all the mechanical\Nbits and bobs are left alone.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.15,0:25:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The bodies, however,\N most certainly aren't.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.99,0:25:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They can chop your car in half,\Nadd a four-foot section in the middle,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.55,0:26:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}completely re-equip\Nthe interior, and in the process,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.46,0:26:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}lighten your wallet to the tune\Nof half a million pounds.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.71,0:26:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Semi-shake money buys\Nhand-crafted wooden door cappings,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.39,0:26:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}or maybe some of the endless gizmos.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.63,0:26:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In fact, they'll do anything a customer\Nwants, providing they're not asked to{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.25,0:26:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}wander off too deeply\Ninto the realms of poor taste.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.59,0:26:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A Rolls-Royce beach buggy,\Nfor instance, is considered to be{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.95,0:26:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}on the wrong side of the borderline.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.42,0:26:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}However, it seems a purple car\Nwith a Dralon interior is not.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.10,0:26:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,- We often fit quite outrageous styles\Nand colors, but of course that very much
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.77,0:26:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,depends on where the car's going\Nand the environment it's going to be in.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.78,0:26:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,80)}So it's very difficult\Nfor us to take a decision
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.33,0:26:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,80)}and say that a particular car\Nis outlandish or unrealistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.98,0:26:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very, very important to be mindful of their particular circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.50,0:26:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARKSON: {\i1}So what\Nare these circumstances?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.18,0:27:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Well, obviously a great many do\Nend up in places like Saudi Arabia,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.89,0:27:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}where 24-carat gold-plated everything\Nis not deemed vulgar.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.22,0:27:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But a fair few stay at home.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.07,0:27:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a package where they literally\Nhooperised, as they term it, the vehicle,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.82,0:27:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,from the point of view of the internal\Nwork on walnut veneer,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.49,0:27:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the various picnic tables\Nand drinks cabinets.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.62,0:27:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a double CD installed\Nwithin the console.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.53,0:27:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the front spoilers of Valance and a\Nfew other external appearances which set
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.87,0:27:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the car apart from other normal\NBentleys and Rolls-Royces.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.94,0:27:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bentley car is a driver's car,\Nand I just felt that if I wanted a tourer,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.15,0:27:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it's just driving around London\Nand the South East or going abroad,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.26,0:27:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,then I might as well equip it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.79,0:27:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- There's just something\Nvery special about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.26,0:27:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They give us the extra\Nthings that we need.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.13,0:27:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just special colors, but special\Nthings like our back window, which has
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.67,0:27:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,been colored slightly because\NI don't like the sun too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.94,0:28:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a very, very special chauffeur\Nwho looks after the cars
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.19,0:28:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,rather as if they're his children.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.83,0:28:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- Frankly, you can't blame anyone\Nfor treating these cars like children.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.23,0:28:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I mean, this began in life as one of the\Nmost expensive production cars ever and{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.47,0:28:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}now costs, what, two, three times more?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.21,0:28:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Whether you like the hooperisation\Nprogramme or not, remember,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.17,0:28:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}there's still a Bentley turbo underneath.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.31,0:28:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Somewhere.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.78,0:28:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you happen to fancy that Bentley,\Nyou're in luck because it is for sale.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.95,0:28:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only two years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.14,0:28:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's being offered at £114,000.\NObviously, a mere snip at the price.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.66,0:28:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all for this week.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.87,0:28:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Next week, we've got a report\Non easing traffic congestion,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.78,0:28:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,we look at the latest work\Non improving motorcycle safety,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.54,0:28:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,we road test the new Honda Concerto,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.18,0:28:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and we look at three-wheelers.\NSo, see you next week.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.26,0:28:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Same time, same place.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.42,0:28:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, drive safely. Good night.
